instruction:
Compute the derivative of the implicit function:
$$
2 \cdot y^4 - \frac{ 3 \cdot x + 3 \cdot y }{ 2 \cdot x - 2 \cdot y } = 0
$$

Options:
A. -\frac{y^2}{2\cdot\left(x^2+y^2\right)+x\cdot y}
B. -\frac{y^2}{2\cdot\left(x^2-y^2\right)+3\cdot x\cdot y}
C. -\frac{y^2}{2\cdot\left(x^2-y^2\right)-2\cdot x\cdot y}
D. -\frac{y^2}{2\cdot\left(x^2-y^2\right)+x\cdot y}
E. -\frac{y^2}{2\cdot\left(x^2+y^2\right)-x\cdot y}
F. -\frac{y^2}{2\cdot\left(x^2-y^2\right)+2\cdot x\cdot y}
G. -\frac{y^2}{2\cdot\left(x^2-y^2\right)-x\cdot y}
H. -\frac{y^2}{2\cdot\left(x^2-y^2\right)-3\cdot x\cdot y}
